# PLC Decoder Pro — Project Summary

## What Was Built

A complete, production-grade Python desktop application for decoding Mitsubishi FX5U / LiraNET protocol PLC hex data into formatted Excel reports.

## Key Discoveries from Your Reference Files

| Finding | Detail |
|---|---|
| Protocol | **LiraNET Data Transmission Protocol on EtherNET** (`mrpl@2016`) |
| PLC Model | **Mitsubishi FX5U** (Little-Endian data storage) |
| Packet Start | `03E9` = Sub-Client ID 1001 |
| Timestamp | 7 words: Year/Month/Day/Hour/Minute/Second/MS (big-endian 16-bit) |
| Sample data | `03E9 07E8 000B 000B 000A 0037 0011 001E` = ID=1001, 2024-11-11 10:55:17.030 |
| Registers | D1600–D1710 (20 registers, 9999 = sentinel "no data") |

## Project Structure (35 files)

```
PLC-Decoder/
├── main.py                     ← Entry point (GUI + CLI)
├── requirements.txt
├── README.md
├── parser/
